Maintainer: Emilio L. Cano <emilio.lopez@urjc.es>
Description: {dsexams} creates questions to develop specialized exercise "templates".
 It follows a data-science approach, both for the generation and for the teaching.
 The templates are randomly generated including exercises, their solutions 
 (using probability distributions to produce data or sampling for exercise options) 
 and domain-specific feedback. {dsexams} is built upon the {exams} package and expanded
 for generating specific content based on a data model and keywords.
 This approach can be used to create Virtual Classroom quizzes to provide a stimulus to students who 
 will never repeat exercises as in the hackneyed "problem sheets". Using the 
 template, new questionaires can be used to increase the Data Science community question bank.
